ltures in the 1960s literary works of three renowned authors are examined: Savushun, Drama der Trauer by Simin Daneshvar (Iran), La Plaça del Diamant by Rodoreda (Spain), and Der geteilte Himmel by Christa Wolf (GDR). Based on these shared stories from under the authoritarian regimes of the Shah, General Franco and the communist authorities in East Germany, Yahya Kouroshi illuminates the subject of modernity from a cross-cultural perspective and traces the diverse developments from and alternatives to this global cultural and social phenomenon.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAuthorsxPolitical and social views. 0aPolitics and literature. 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aChrista Wolf. 4aInterkulturalität. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMercè Rodoreda. 4aNeuzeitliches Denken. 4aSimin Daneshvar. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literature 2014z9783110370331oZDB-23-DLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014z9783111025223oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383762622340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839426227?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839426227423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839426227/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11